description=<H1><ORANGE>SIEGE NIGHT v2.7.0
description=<BR>
description=<WHITE>Every night could be your last. Siege Night turns your base into a battleground.
description=<BR>
description=Escalating siege nights with wave-based attacks, directional hordes, special zombies (Sprinters, Breakers, Tanks), noise-triggered mini-hordes, kill tracking, chat commands, vote system, and full siege history.
description=<BR>
description=Built for fortress defense - solo or multiplayer.
description=<BR>
description=<YELLOW>Features:
description=<BR>
description=<WHITE>- Two-layer wave system: surge waves + baseline tide that never stops
description=- Directional attacks from a random compass direction each siege
description=- Per-group independent sieges in MP (separate waves, direction, kills)
description=- Special zombies after midnight (Sprinters, Breakers, Tanks)
description=- Safehouse anchor mode - zombies target your base even if you leave
description=- Noise-triggered mini-hordes with attractor tracking between siege nights
description=- Chat commands: !siege start, stop, status, next, vote
description=- Vote system for MP - any player can call a vote, majority needed
description=- 30+ sandbox options across 3 sandbox pages
description=- Kill tracking + siege history panel in character info
description=- Debug tools (Numpad keys) for testing
description=<BR>
description=<RED>Report bugs on the Workshop page!
